---
description: Ask before risky or wide-impact changes
globs: ["**/*.{ts,tsx,js,jsx,json,sql,yml,yaml}"]
alwaysApply: true
---

Do not make risky changes silently.

Risky changes include:
- changing UI structure
- changing styles
- changing navigation
- renaming files, routes, components, props, or folders
- changing database queries or mutation behavior
- changing authentication behavior
- changing membership, wallet, gift, payment, or balance logic
- changing live-streaming flow
- changing animation timing or overlay sequencing
- introducing or removing dependencies
- moving code across files
- changing deployment or infrastructure assumptions

If a task would require one of these:
- stop first
- state exactly what would change
- propose the smallest safe option
- prefer a local fix instead of a broad rewrite

Default behavior:
no silent high-impact changes.
